<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="fortunate-adj">fortunate <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'fɔːtʃənət/    美 /'fɔːrtʃənət/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-lucky">1.★ <strong>幸运的；吉利的 (lucky)：</strong></h4>
<p>反 unfortunate / unlucky </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a fortunate event 
吉利事</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Red is a fortunate colour in Chinese culture.
在中国文化中，红色是喜庆的颜色。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) fortunate to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Recently, I was <strong>fortunate enough to</strong> travel to South Africa.
最近，我有幸去了南非旅游。</p><footer>译林⑥ – 4</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) fortunate in doing sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He's fortunate in having a good job.
他真幸运，有份好工作。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) fortunate + that 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It was fortunate that the lost painting was recovered.
幸运的是遗失的画被找回来了。</p></div></div>